data.description: PRICE REDUCED... Bring Your Best Offer! Also, SELLER WILL PAY $1,450 and $550 ONE-TIME HOA ASSESSMENT FEE TOWARDS THE BUYER'S CLOSING COST. Home is located minutes from HWY 200, food shopping, restaurants, hospitals, etc. Marion Landing, 55+ community offers plenty of activities such as swimming pool, fitness center, 8 lanes bowling, tennis, social gathering, pickleball, and much more. Home featured two bedrooms, two bathrooms, carpet and vinyl flooring, hallway linen closet, skylight in the kitchen and bathrooms, kitchen with breakfast nook, combo formal dinning & family room, inside laundry room with storage cabinets, gutter, pipe, electrical outlet outside, 12x14 enclosed patio, 12x9 outside storage room with electrical hookup , 19x 20 two car space carport. Master bedroom: stand up shower, 4x9 walk-in closet/glass sliding door, skylight in the bathroom, window, towel/closet, double vanity.  Guest bedroom: walk-in closet, shower/tub, single vanity, vinyl flooring. New electrical panel-01/2023, Roof replaced-10/2003, Hot-Water Heater-04/2003, AC-06/2005.
